cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
1. cs.RO (Robotics) - The paper deals with the problem of perception and manipulation of articulated objects by robots, which is a core problem in robotics. 
2. cs.CV (Computer Vision) - The proposed approach involves using RGBD sensor data to estimate the poses of articulated objects, which is a common problem in computer vision. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The use of nonparametric belief propagation algorithm for pose estimation can be considered as an AI technique. 
4. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The proposed approach involves iterative estimation of object-part pose beliefs, which can be seen as a machine learning problem. 
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper deals with the problem of controlling robots to manipulate articulated objects, which can be considered as a systems and control problem.
